name: youtube-search-python
summary: search for youtube videos, channels & playlists & get video information using link without youtube data api v3
documentation_summary: The GitHub repository "alexmercerind/youtube-search-python" provides a Python library for searching YouTube videos, channels, and playlists without using the YouTube Data API v3. It allows users to retrieve video and playlist information using links and get search suggestions. The project, which was archived by the owner on June 30, 2022, and is now read-only, supports both synchronous and asynchronous searches. It includes features for filtering search results, getting next page search results, and retrieving video information using video links or IDs. The library is licensed under the MIT license and was designed to simulate requests made by YouTube's web client, focusing on JSON responses rather than HTML content.
